description:
&lt;p&gt;Rotary Ward is a 16 bedded ward for elective surgical patients on green pathway, for all specialities at the William Harvey Hospital (Surgery &amp; Anaesthetics). We also have ENT outpatients department attached to the ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a full time Registered Nurse to join our team. You will have the opportunity to learn and develop your skills in dealing with a variety of surgical conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a hardworking motivated nurse with a passion to learn and deliver excellent care to join our friendly team – our aim is to provide safe and effective care that exceeds the expectations of our patients and the public and who will embrace our Trust values –&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;People feel cared for as individuals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;People feel safe, reassured and involved&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;People feel teamwork; trust and respect sit at the heart of everything we do&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;People feel confident we are making a difference&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Sarah Button, Job title: Acting Ward Manager, Email address: sarahbutton@nhs.net, Telephone number: 01233 616260&lt;/p&gt;
